					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Vellum codex; Ashkenazi (French) square and semi-cursive script of 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex. </support>
								<extent>279 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>265</height>
										<width>185</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>155/160 </height>
										<width>110/115</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>Hebrew foliation starts on folio 6, ends on folio 271. </p>
									<p>279 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves and a parchment flyleaf at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>36 quires: i3, ii8, iii8, iv8, v8, vi8, vii8, viii8, ix12-1, x8, xi8, xii8, xiii8, xiv8, xv8, xvi8, xvii8, xviii8, xix8, xx8, xxi8, xxii8, xxiii8, xxiv8, xxv8, xxvi2, xxvii8, xxviii8, xxix8, xxx8, xxxi8, xxxii8, xxxiii8, xxxiv8, xxxv8, xxxvi6.</p>
									<p>There is confusion in the collation due to a later re-binding: folio 2-3 (maybe folio 1 as well) were initially at the end of the codex as the earlier pencil foliation and quire numbering with Roman numbers demonstrate.</p>
									<p>Quires marked by catchwords, often decorated, in some cases cut away in the trimming. </p>
									<p>Edges colored red.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="3" ruledLines="45" writtenLines="44">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Pricking and ruling are often visible.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
